CLIP DESCRIPTION:
Dressed in disguise, Rostov (Richard Lynch) pretends to welcome a boat of refugees while really interested in the goods below deck.

FILM DESCRIPTION:
This red-baiting action film stars Chuck Norris as Matt Hunter, a retired CIA agent who lives in the Florida Everglades. A communist invasion of Miami brings Hunter out of retirement to fight the encroaching hordes led by everyone's favorite low-budget bad guy, Richard Lynch. The film is extremely jingoistic, presenting the evil communists staging an invasion on Christmas, demolishing a church, and attempting to blow up a school bus full of children. From the same school of thinking which produced Rambo and Red Dawn, this film at least features some convincing gore by makeup wizard Tom Savini (Friday the 13th), working on his third gig for director Joseph Zito. Zito and Savini returned with Red Scorpion.

Selected as the opening night film for Sundance 2012, HELLO I MUST BE GOING features acclaimed actress Melanie Lynskey (WIN WIN, UP IN THE AIR, TWO AND A HALF MEN) in her breakout role as Amy, a recent divorcee who seeks refuge in the suburban Connecticut home of her parents (Blythe Danner and John Rubinstein). hfbYg57-puk.description:
Scott Cawthon updated his website once again, giving us another horrifying first look at a FNAF 4 Nightmare animatronic - this time it's Foxy!

In this video I look closely at the details of the new Foxy the Pirate image and talk about what it could entail for the story of Five Nights at Freddy's 4.

There are a lot of hidden secrets in this image, such as the word 'NIGHTMARE' hidden in Foxy's teeth, the phrase 'OUT OF ORDER' at the bottom left, and the numbers 8 and 7 hidden in his right eye. 

All this definitely points to the Bite of '87, and I personally believe it labels Foxy as the culprit! I'd still love to know what you guys think about what I talked about and debate it in the comment section. 

I'm so pumped for this game now - can't believe there is still five months to go! I don't know if I'll actually have the guts to play though... hah.
